main event: A witness reported seeing an unidentified object descending rapidly toward the horizon in Del Mar, California on November 2-11, 1961.
interesting points: The witness indicated the object moved erratically and had an intensity much brighter than the surrounding stars., The sighting lasted approximately 3 seconds., A total of five similar sightings by multiple witnesses were reported., Witnesses expressed that the object was not reflective light but a self-luminous source., The conclusion speculated the sighting could have been caused by meteors or artificial fireballs.
sighted object: bright white or bluish-white disc-shaped object
witness description: The witness had prior experience as an FM observer at Lindbergh Field, San Diego.
